descript.abstract: This line feature class is the combined collection of the street centerlines created by the San Luis Obispo regions various GIS agencies and quality control checked by Contact One.
descript.purpose: This street centerline layer was developed with the purpose of being deployed in a centralized database to and to be maintained by each of the responsible jurisdictions in San Luis Obispo County.

theme.themekt: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

idinfo.accconst: There are no restrictions and legal prerequisites for accessing this feature class.
idinfo.useconst: There are no restrictions and legal prerequisites for using the feature class after access is granted.

cntinfo.cntinst: Any questions about the metadata for the roads_master layer please send and email to jberrie@contactone.com

idinfo.datacred: CMRS, City of Atascadero, City of Grover Beach, City of Paso Robles, City of Pismo Beach, City of San Luis Obispo, MSAG database, CalFire, CalTrans, SLO Assessors Office, NAIP, Contact One.
idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.3000

horizpa.horizpar: All spatial adjustment for this street centerline layer were made based upon the 1 foot and 6 inch imagery provided by San Luis Obispo County and the 2009 NAIP imagery.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Length of feature in internal units.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

cntaddr.addrtype: REQUIRED: The mailing and/or physical address for the organization or individual.
cntaddr.city: REQUIRED: The city of the address.
cntaddr.state: REQUIRED: The state or province of the address.
cntaddr.postal: REQUIRED: The ZIP or other postal code of the address.
